-- ADP Will Acquire Cobalt for $400 Million to Add Digital Marketing Programs
-- Katie Hoffmann
-- 2010-07-09T15:06:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/adp-will-acquire-cobalt-for-400-million-to-add-digital-marketing-programs.html

          
          
             Automatic Data Processing Inc. , a
business outsourcing service provider, agreed to acquire closely
held Cobalt for about $400 million in cash, gaining digital
marketing programs for automakers.  
 The deal may be completed in four to six weeks and add to
earnings in the first year, Roseland, New Jersey-based ADP said
today in a statement.  
 ADP Chief Executive Officer  Gary Butler  is expanding
offerings to automakers and dealers beyond services such as
managing accounting or inventory. Sales to dealers represent
more than 15 percent of the companyâ€™s revenue.  
 ADP rose 23 cents to $40.60 at 11:04 a.m. New York time in
Nasdaq Stock Market trading. The shares had fallen 5.7 percent
this year before today.  
